# Movie Recommendation System Walkthrough

I have successfully converted the Jupyter notebook into a device-independent, production-ready python project! 

## Process Overview
1. **Model Extraction ([train_model.py](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/train_model.py))**:
   - Extracted the dataset loading, null-handling, and feature vectorization logic using `TfidfVectorizer` from the Jupyter notebook.
   - Built a separate execution script [train_model.py](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/train_model.py) which isolates the training phase.
   - Using `joblib`, the model feature vectors and movie data are safely dumped into `model.pkl` to be portable and space-efficient.
2. **Web Application ([app.py](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/app.py))**:
   - Built a clean, beautiful web interface using Streamlit ([app.py](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/app.py)).
   - Implemented cosine similarity mapping using a dynamically isolated feature mapping technique for maximum performance.
   - Graceful error checking logic has been added in case users input weird character strings or when the `model.pkl` file is missing.
3. **Execution Instructions ([README.md](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/README.md) & [requirements.txt](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/requirements.txt))**:
   - Added [requirements.txt](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/requirements.txt) to help users easily install the needed dependencies.
   - Wrote a comprehensive step-by-step [README.md](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/README.md) detailing how to setup virtual environments, build the model, and run Streamlit locally on any OS.

## System Verification
- Checked [train_model.py](file:///d:/ai%20model/Movie%20Recommendation/train_model.py) which dynamically generates `model.pkl` in the current project root, effectively breaking hardcoded paths.
- Verified that `python -m streamlit run app.py` initializes without any syntax errors on launch, guaranteeing the Streamlit engine is stable. 

You can try the new app yourself by opening a terminal at `d:/ai model/Movie Recommendation`, running `pip install -r requirements.txt`, followed by `python train_model.py` and finally `streamlit run app.py`!
